{{!--
  conditional-armor.hbs  —  Honest per-damage-type ("conditional") stopping power.

  The main armor panel (armor-display.hbs) now shows the CONVENTIONAL SP a normal hit meets (typed-only
  layers excluded). This sub-panel surfaces the EXTRA protection a worn typed layer (Chromebook fire
  armor, a radiation-hardened suit, …) grants ONLY against its own damage type — the same per-type value
  module/combat/DamageApplicator.js `_deriveLiveSP` feeds the damage math, so display and resolved hit
  always agree. Built by module/mech/typed-armor-display.js.

  Context:
    conditionalSP = { <type>: { <HitLoc>: SP, … }, … }  — only types/locations that ADD protection.
  The include (combat.hbs) is guarded on system.conditionalSP, so this partial renders only when a worn
  typed layer beats the conventional total somewhere. The type keys are the closed fire/radiation/heat
  enum the damage dialog offers; label each with its existing dialog label.
--}}
<section class="cp-conditional-armor">
  <header>
    <h3 title="{{CPLocal 'ConditionalArmorHint'}}">{{CPLocal "ConditionalArmorHeader"}}</h3>
  </header>

  {{#each conditionalSP as |locs type|}}
  <div class="field cp-conditional-row">
    <label class="cp-conditional-type">
      {{~#if (equals type "fire")}}{{CPLocal "DamageDlgTypeFire"}}{{/if~}}
      {{~#if (equals type "radiation")}}{{CPLocal "DamageDlgTypeRadiation"}}{{/if~}}
      {{~#if (equals type "heat")}}{{CPLocal "DamageDlgTypeHeat"}}{{/if~}}
    </label>
    <span class="flex-pad"></span>
    <span class="cp-conditional-locs">
      {{#each locs as |sp loc|}}
      <span class="cp-conditional-loc" title="{{CPLocal 'SPFull'}}">{{shortCPLocal loc}}&nbsp;{{sp}}</span>
      {{/each}}
    </span>
  </div>
  {{/each}}
</section>
